    kmeans=KMeans(n_clusters=i)
    kmeans.fit(df[['Annual Income (k$)']])
    inertia_scores.append(kmeans.inertia_)

In [98]:
inertia_scores_bivariate=[]
for i in range(1,11):
    kmeans_bivariate=KMeans(n_clusters=i)
    kmeans_bivariate.fit(df[['Annual Income (k$)','Spending Score (1-100)']])
    inertia_scores_bivariate.append(kmeans_bivariate.inertia_)
plt.plot(range(1,11),inertia_scores_bivariate)
#From this we can see the 'elbow' at 5 so therefore we want 5 clusters
